    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nthis runtime contains rust.vim which doesn't work at all and its python related things slow down the startup time of  python\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nsudo add-apt-repository ppa:neovim-ppa/unstable \r\nsudo apt install neovim\r\n\r\nls /usr/share/nvim/runtime\r\n\r\nI have to manually delete:\r\n\r\n- sudo rm /usr/share/nvim/runtime/ftplugin/rust.vim\r\n- sudo rm /usr/share/nvim/runtime/rust*\r\n\r\nto removing the wierd rust related commands\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nremove those things which don't work anymore\r\n\r\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.1 Build type: Debug LuaJIT 2.1.1713484068 Run \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nLinux Mint (ubuntu22.04)\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nalacritty 0.12.2 (9d9982df)\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\ntmux-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\napt",
